# 2279 - echo
# Read any number of characters and output them exactly
# Hint: After input stream ends, input is all 0

# Initialize mem[0] = 1 to detect end of input
[0]<1

# Read input character
A<I

# Check if A == 0 (end of input)
# Load mem[A] - if A==0, gets 1, otherwise 0
Z<[A]

# Output A (this executes even if Z is set, but halt happens after current cycle)
O<A

# Program loops back to start
# When A==0, Z was set to 1, so it will halt
